						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and not dated. It refers to the Vijayanagara king <hi rend="bold">Achyutadēva-Mahārāya</hi> and states that some lands in the village <hi rend="bold">Yāḷape,</hi> together with a fixed amount of toll-revenue on betel leaves, grains and the like in the <hi rend="italic">ṭhāṇya</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Rūpalaguḍi</hi> were granted for the service of the god [Nārā]yaṇadēva. </p>						

